args: She shone more brilliantly than\nanyone I'd ever seen.
She was as a beautiful rose,\nblooming in the summer sun.
It's so hot... I'm burning up! How much\nlonger until we get to the beach?
Griping and moaning will not make it\nany cooler. More walking, less talking.
Mew wouldn't understand, Chelle...\nMew with your convenient outfit changes...
But my beautiful, fluffy fur makes the heat\nsimply clawful!
*sigh* This is what happens when\nyou bumble about like that.
My deepest apologies for this FERAL\nfeline's behavior. Are you unharmed?
Oh, I'm so sorry! I've just never seen\nanyone as pretty as you before, Miss.
My! Aren't you the sweetest thing? Go on,\nCat Sìth. You owe her an apology.
To be fair, though, Chelle, SHE was the\none spacing out in the middle of the road.
Interested in the upper windows of this\nmansion, are we? It's the mayor's house,\nI believe.
If I recall, the mayor has a son. Could it\nbe that you have your heart set on him?
I'm just looking, though. We live\nin two different worlds, after all...
So you won't do it if I don't order you?\nI just thought...
So it's a problem of social standing.
A cat could easily make it from this wall\nto the window frame, couldn't it, Cat Sìth?
Then I'd like one of my kittens to come\nhere. One who is nimble, if you would.\nDon't keep me waiting.
Mew use your kittens for everything,\nI swear.
Do you know how to write?
A little is enough. Now, come along.\nWe must procure some stationery.
To make up for that little collision earlier,\nI will lend you my assistance.
I'm quite skilled with these matters.
*pant* I finally found you!\nThe lady from before!
Ah, we meet again.\nHow do you do?
I'm okay...\nBut that doesn't matter! Look at this!
Oh, he responded to our letter.\nWhat seems to be the problem?
That's just it—he REPLIED to my\nLETTER! And he said he wanted me to\nsend another one! What are we gonna do?!

I anticipated he might. After all,
he received a strange letter from
a cat on his windowsill, with such
perfectly refined contents...
Anyone would want to know who sent it.\nEspecially a curious boy his age.
Heavens, no. But there are plenty of things\none can infer without having met a person.
Wow... It feels like you know him better\nthan I do.
He actually saved me once, you know.
Some items went missing at a storefront\nand everyone thought I was the thief.
I'm an orphan, and I'm really poor, so I\ndidn't have anyone who would vouch for\nme.
But he was there. And he was on my side.
I thought I'd be happy just gazing up at\nhim from the road, but after his reply,\nI wanna know more about him...
You've always been by my side.\nYou've always protected me.\nYou're the only one I can trust.
This is not an order.\nBut I want you to listen...
Chelle came here to be on holiday.\nShe simply cannot be troubled with—
Very well. With my genius, I will make\ncertain that he returns your affection.
What is the meowning of this?\nWhy are mew looking after this street rat?
Because social standing is of no\nconsequence when it comes to\nmatters of the heart.
...Um, Miss? What do you mean?\nAre you someone super important?
...That is irrelevant to the matter at hand.
I'm naught but a friendly stranger helping\nyou with your love life. That's all you need\nto know, is it not?
Excellent. Then let us begin your lesson\nin summer love!
And so our story began...\nA story of a shimmering,\nbeautiful summer with her.
